OL,3,CEast Midlands schools 'long way off'
OL,4,Cwork experience targets, report finds
OL,6,FOne of the most commonly-heard
OL,7,Fcriticisms levelled at schools in this
OL,8,Fcountry is that they don't prepare
OL,9,Fyoung people well enough for the world
OL,10,Fof work.
OL,12,FIt's often said that students come out
OL,13,Fof their school years lacking the
OL,14,F"soft" skills needed to succeed in the
OL,15,Fworkplace.
OL,17,FThe Government says meaningful work
OL,18,Fexperience is key to helping teenagers
OL,19,Fmake the transition from education
OL,20,Finto work.
